		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Beaufort So. Ca.</placeName> <date>Sept. 26<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1834</date></p>
			<p>Most Revd. Sir</p>
		  <p rend="indent(2)">Your fame has travelld. with your work.  You are known as one<lb/> of the few whose <sic>lifes</sic> have been devoted to the <sic>defence</sic> of Judaism&#58; will it be<lb/> an assurance for a stranger to ask one question&#63;  I am a Jew&#59; and thank God[&#63;]<lb/> gloring in being such&#59; not one&#44; though&#44; who cares not for the faith&#59; but desirous<lb/> of diving into those mysteries&#44; that cannot possibly&#44; by any human being&#44;<lb/> to solved&#59; yet&#44; the object&#44; which&#44; some may try to obtain.  I live in a place not<lb/> much known&#59; but whose inhabitants <del>are</del> &#40;excluding Israelites&#41; are there [&#63;]<lb/> christians&#44;&#8211;that is&#44; members of the church&#59; consequently &#40;I am&#41; subject to the utmost<lb/> scrutiny&#44; frequently have I been calld. on by some to ascertain the general<lb/> belief of the israelites&#59; and certainly give such answers as will make to app<lb/>&#45;ear their generosity&#44; without regard to prejudice&#59; but often have I been asked<lb/> about their saviour&#58; whether we believe he has come or not.  I answer<lb/> as my parents &amp; common sense teacher&#44; and the &#34;Bible&#34; directs&#59; but com&#45;<lb/>monly ask if we believe he has [&#63;] appeared as the &#34;the deemer of mankind&#34;<lb/> generally.  Now all fair persons must admit&#44; sir&#44; that what is handed<lb/> down through books&#44; excepting those fictitious works that extravagance<lb/> will teach us not to believe should be somewhat suspected&#58;  wed. surely be<lb/> put down by one <sic>incredillous</sic> class if we would not put any con&#45;<lb/>fidence in the new testament&#59; yet&#44; a common work—an history<lb/> of the revolution—it&#39;s contents are believed more particularly&#44; as con[&#63;]<lb/> with facts that are plainly proven&#58; and what the difference with the<lb/> new testament&#63;  What further proof is required than that the christians<lb/> exist&#63;  their doctrine in some respects is fair&#44; I mean their inclinations<lb/> to do good&#59; but I want to know how the &#34;Jews&#34; exist in relation<lb/> to <persName>Jesus</persName>—or Christians.  If you&#39;ll only deign to answer this humble<lb/> request of one who values your talents&#59; reveres your name&#59; con[&#63;]<lb/> your zeal in behalf of the despised&#59; &#40;though thank God that opprobi[&#63;]<lb/>tering is nearly done away with&#41; Revd Sir yours &amp;c holy  <persName role="author">D. Jacobs</persName></p>

		<pb n="2"/>
			
			<p>PS&#58; postage I&#39;ll pay of all Letters on ac of this correspondence&#59; that I may<lb/> not be too <sic>burthensome</sic> to an utter stranger of the subscriber<lb/> In the above I forgot to ask whether <persName>Jesus</persName>—came for the purpose of<lb/> redeeming the Jews with other&#39;s of mankind.&#8211;</p>

		<pb n="4"/>
		
			<p>The <addressee>Rev. Mr. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p>care of <persName>Mr. Hackenbry</persName></p>
